# SiteRoast design system

## Tokens (source of truth)
- All colors come from **CSS variables** in `src/app/globals.css` on **`:root[data-theme="light"]` / `:root[data-theme="dark"]`** (hex/rgba via `next-themes` `data-theme` on `<html>`): `background`, `foreground`, `surface-1..3`, `primary`, `accent`, `muted`, `border`, `chart-1..5`, sidebar aliases, semantic `success` / `warning` / `destructive`.
- Do **not** use raw Tailwind palette classes (`zinc-*`, `slate-*`, arbitrary hex) for theme colors in components.
- Shadows: prefer `shadow-surface-xs` / `shadow-surface-sm` from utilities; use `glow-primary-soft` sparingly for hero accents.

## Typography
- **Inter** via `font-sans` for UI, headings, body, buttons, nav.
- **JetBrains Mono** via `font-mono` for metrics, calculator values, code, tabular numbers (`tabular-nums`).

## Icons
- **lucide-react** only; default stroke **1.5** (e.g. `[&_svg]:stroke-[1.5]` on parents or `IconFrame`).
- Use `IconFrame` (`src/components/ui/icon-frame.tsx`) for feature cards, nav accents, and report section headers where icons need a container.

## Components
- Primitives live under `src/components/ui/` (shadcn-style). Prefer `Button`, `Card`, `Badge`, `Input`, `Tabs`, `Alert`, `Dialog`, `Sheet` with token-based classes.
- Authenticated app shell: **`AuthenticatedShell`** wraps `SidebarProvider` → `Sidebar` (**`AppSidebar`**) → `SidebarInset`. The desktop **`Sidebar`** uses a **flex spacer** matching `--sidebar-width` plus a fixed panel; **main content stays in `SidebarInset`** (`min-w-0`, scroll on the inset). Prefer this over ad-hoc `SidebarProvider` copies on pages.

## Layout
- Do **not** use `margin-left` hacks (e.g. `ml-[14.4rem]`) next to the sidebar; **spacer + fixed rail** reserves width (`--sidebar-width` from [`src/lib/shell-layout.ts`](src/lib/shell-layout.ts)).
- **`AuthenticatedShell`**: main fills **`SidebarInset`** (no default centered **`max-w-[min(…,88rem)]`** / **`mx-auto`**). Use **`constrainContentWidth`** only for narrow flows (e.g. checkout **`max-w-[min(100%,72rem)]`** + **`mx-auto`**).

## Charts
- In-app charts read CSS variables via `useChartTheme` (`--chart-1` … `--chart-5`). Do not hardcode chart colors in components.

## PDF / static HTML
- Server-side report styling uses `reportHex` in `src/lib/report-theme.ts`. When changing app tokens, update `reportHex` in the same PR so exports stay on-brand.
